                    </li>
                </ul>
                </p>
            </div>
            <!-- Applications of Design Thinking -->
            <div>
                <h3>
                    Applications of Design Thinking
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Design thinking can be applied to a wide range of problems and challenges. It is commonly used in
                    product development, but it can also be used in other areas such as service design, organizational
                    change, and social innovation.
                    <br>
                    Here are some examples of how design thinking can be applied:
                <ol class="h5">
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            Product Development:
                        </b>
                        Design thinking can be used to develop new products or improve existing ones. By understanding
                        the
                        user’s needs and challenges, teams can develop products that meet those needs.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            Service Design:
                        </b>
                        Design thinking can be used to design services that meet the user’s needs. By understanding the
                        user’s journey and pain points, teams can develop services that are more effective and
                        efficient.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            Organizational Change:
                        </b>
                        Design thinking can be used to drive organizational change. By involving employees in the change
                        process and understanding their needs and challenges, teams can develop solutions that are more
                        effective.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            Social Innovation:
                        </b>
                        Design thinking can be used to address social challenges such as poverty, healthcare, and
                        education.
                        By understanding the needs of communities and developing solutions that meet those needs, teams
                        can
                        create positive social impact.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </div>
