                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            To Have the intention to improve products & services:
                        </b>
                        analyse and understand how users interact with the products or services to investigate the
                        conditions in which
                        they operate.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>
                            By Asking significant questions and challenge assumption:
                        </b>
                        out of the box thinking is too falsify previous assumptions that is to make it possible to prove
                        whether or not
                        they Are valid. and also by digging a bit deeper into problem solving. And thus, Design thinking
                        techniques and
                        strategies belong at every level of business
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The process of design thinking is firmly based on how you can generate a holistic and empathic
                        understanding
                        of the problem that people or users face.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Design thinking involves ambiguous and inherently subjective concepts such as emotions needs
                        motivations and drivers of behaviour. Which makes Design thinking both an art and a science. It
                        combines investigations into ambiguous elements of the problem with rational and analytical
                        research.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                </p>
